Package: ppmm
Title: Function of Proxy pattern-mixture models (PPMM) (One Line, Title Case)
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(person("Rebecca", "Andridge", email = "andridge.1@osu.edu", role = c("aut","cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-9991-9647")),
             person("Ruoqi", "Song", email = "song.1344@osu.edu", role = c("aut"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-5771-2103")),
             person("Brady", "West", email = "bwest@umich.edu", role = c("aut"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-0160-1388")))
Description: An easy-to-install and user-friendly tool for conducting sensitivity analysis on microdata or summary statistics, supporting both continuous and binary outcomes. The tool leverages a proxy pattern-mixture model framework and offers flexibility to perform analyses using either Maximum Likelihood Estimation (MLE) or Bayesian inference (one paragraph).
